This paper discusses the WiFi MAC architecture and its support for aggregation, which is primarily related to networking (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also touches upon the security implications of aggregation, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-offs involved in aggregation, which can be seen as a system-level optimization problem (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of aggregation in multimedia applications, which can be related to multimedia systems (cs.MM).
